1. Create a new Python virtual environment by running the following command:
=> python3 -m venv openai_env
Summary: This will create a new virtual environment in a directory called openai_env.

2. Activate the virtual environment by running:
=> source openai_env/bin/activate

3. Once the virtual environment is activated, you can install OpenAI Python v0.27.0 using pip:
=> pip install openai==0.27.0
Summary: This will install the specific version of the OpenAI Python library.

4. Once the installation is complete, you can verify that the correct version of the library is installed by running:
=> pip show openai
Summary: This should display information about the installed package, including the version number.
